gomodel:SYNGO_5266  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1, 2 (and suppl.): immunofluorescence imaging of overexpressed myc-tagged LIMK1 in cultured hippocampal neurons showed enrichment in dendritic spines. Using various mutant constructs, authors showed that targeting to the dendritic spine is driven by LIMK1's palmitoyl-motif.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Human LIMK1 and LIMK2 cDNAs were from Arizona State University plasmid repository. A C-terminal myc tag was added to LIMK1 and LIMK2 by PCR and the resultant fragments were subcloned into the mammalian expression vector pRK5 and the lentiviral vector FUW (Lois et al., 2002). CCSS-LIMK1-myc (Cys 7, 8 of LIMK1 mutated to Ser), SC-LIMK1-myc and CS-LIMK1-myc were generated by PCR using mutagenic primers.\"\n\nthe cultured neurons were from rat; \"Hippocampi were dissected from E18 rat embryos and neurons were cultured in Neurobasal/B27 as described\". Doesn't matter much, protein alignment via uniprot online tool showed protein from both species are the same length and have a 95.21% sequence identity." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-09" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5266" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .
